@startuml

title How Campaign Links Work - From Ad Click to Personalized App Experience

start

:== STEP 1: Marketer Creates Campaign ==;

:Marketer creates a campaign in the dashboard;

note right
  Fills in:
  - Name: "Sleep Wellness"
  - iOS URL: https://apps.apple.com/app/id123456
  - Android URL: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.lilly.myapp
  - Fallback URL: https://example.com/landing
  - Source: "facebook"
  - Topic: "sleep"
  - (Optional) iOS Scheme: "lillymobileapp"
  - (Optional) Android Package: "com.lilly.myapp"
  - (Optional) Deep Link Path: "/campaign/{slug}"
end note

:System generates a single tracking link
https://appcampaignpoc.onrender.com/c/sleep-wellness;

:Marketer puts this link in ads
(Facebook, Instagram, Email, etc.);

:== STEP 2: User Clicks the Link ==;

:User sees the ad on their phone and taps
https://appcampaignpoc.onrender.com/c/sleep-wellness;

:Server receives the HTTP request;

note right
  Every request automatically contains:
  - IP address (e.g. 203.0.113.42)
  - User-Agent header (e.g. "Mozilla/5.0
    (iPhone; CPU iPhone OS 18_7...)")
end note

:Server extracts device info from User-Agent;

note right
  User-Agent is parsed into:
  - Device type: "ios" or "android" or "other"
  - OS version: "18.7"
  - Device model: "iphone"
end note

:Server creates a fingerprint hash;

note right
  Fingerprint = SHA-256 hash of:
  "203.0.113.42|ios|18.7|iphone"

  Result: "a3f2b8c9d4e5..."
  (unique per device + network combo)

  This is saved along with:
  - Campaign ID
  - Timestamp (e.g. 10:30:00)
  - Expiry (24 hours later)
  - Consumed: false
end note

if (Deep linking turned on for this campaign?) then (YES)

  if (Device type from User-Agent?) then (iPhone)

    :Server returns an HTML page (not a redirect);

    note right
      The HTML page contains JavaScript that runs:
      window.location.href = "lillymobileapp:///campaign/sleep-wellness"

      This tells the phone: "open the app
      registered to handle lillymobileapp:// URLs"
    end note

    if (App is installed and handles this scheme?) then (YES)
      :iOS opens the app and passes it the URL
      lillymobileapp:///campaign/sleep-wellness;
    else (NO)
      :Nothing happens for 1.5 seconds
      (page checks: document.hidden == false);

      :JavaScript then runs:
      window.location.href = "https://apps.apple.com/app/id123456";

      :User arrives at App Store and installs the app;
    endif

  else (Android)

    :Server returns an HTML page (not a redirect);

    note right
      The HTML page contains JavaScript that runs:
      window.location.href =
      "intent:///campaign/sleep-wellness#Intent;
       scheme=com.lilly.myapp;
       package=com.lilly.myapp;
       S.browser_fallback_url=https://play.google.com/...;
       end"

      This is Android's Intent URI format.
      The browser hands it to the OS automatically.
    end note

    if (App with package com.lilly.myapp installed?) then (YES)
      :Android opens the app directly;
    else (NO)
      :Android reads the browser_fallback_url
      from the Intent URI and navigates to
      https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.lilly.myapp;

      :User arrives at Play Store and installs the app;
    endif

  endif

else (NO - no deep link config)

  if (Device type from User-Agent?) then (iPhone)
    :Server sends HTTP 302 redirect to:
    https://apps.apple.com/app/id123456;
    :Browser instantly goes to App Store;
  elseif (Android) then
    :Server sends HTTP 302 redirect to:
    https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.lilly.myapp;
    :Browser instantly goes to Play Store;
  else (Computer / Other)
    :Server sends HTTP 302 redirect to:
    https://example.com/landing;
    stop
  endif

  :User installs the app from the store;

endif

:== STEP 3: App Launches and Checks Attribution ==;

:User opens the app;

:App sends POST request to:
https://appcampaignpoc.onrender.com/api/v1/attribution/match
with empty body {};

note right
  The request automatically includes
  the phone's IP and User-Agent in
  the HTTP headers (same as before)
end note

:Server generates fingerprint from request headers;

note right
  Same formula as click time:
  SHA-256("203.0.113.42|ios|18.7|iphone")
  = "a3f2b8c9d4e5..."
end note

:Server searches for saved clicks
with this same fingerprint;

:Server filters clicks that are:
- Not consumed (consumed == false)
- Not expired (within 24 hour window)
- Clicked before current time;

if (Any valid clicks found?) then (YES)

  :Server picks the most recent valid click;

  :Server calculates confidence based on time gap;

  note right
    Time between click and app launch:
    - Under 1 hour = "high" confidence
    - 1 to 6 hours = "medium" confidence
    - 6 to 24 hours = "low" confidence
  end note

  :Server marks that click as consumed = true
  (prevents matching again);

  :Server increments install count for this campaign;

  :Server responds with JSON:
  {
    "matched": true,
    "attribution": {
      "campaignId": "550e8400-...",
      "campaignName": "Sleep Wellness",
      "campaignSlug": "sleep-wellness",
      "metadata": {
        "source": "facebook",
        "topic": "sleep"
      },
      "clickedAt": "2026-05-13T10:30:00.000Z",
      "matchConfidence": "high",
      "matchMethod": "fingerprint"
    }
  };

  :App uses this info to personalize the experience
  (e.g. show sleep-related content first);

else (NO)

  :Server responds with JSON:
  {
    "matched": false,
    "attribution": null
  };

  :App shows the normal default experience;

  note right
    This happens when:
    - User never clicked a campaign link, OR
    - Click already consumed on a previous launch, OR
    - Click expired (older than 24 hours), OR
    - User is on a different network (IP changed)
  end note

endif

stop

@enduml
